with my own di&s;tre&s;s! I with a loud &s;cream
fainted away, and when I recovered, found my|&s;elf
in the arms of Mr. Fathom, who wept over
me with great affliction. All his pro&s;pects of
<PB N="299" REF="300">
gaiety had now vani&s;hed, and his heart was
&s;oftened by his own misfortunes, to a feeling of
