<P>She &s;hed a flood of tears at the conclu&s;ion of
this mournful tale which did not fail to affect the
whole audience, e&s;pecially Serafina, who a&s;&s;ured
her, that whatever &s;hould happen to her hus|band,
&s;he might depend upon finding favour and
protection, provided her conduct &s;hould cor|re&s;pond
with her profe&s;&s;ions. While this grate|ful
creature ki&s;&s;ed the hand of her kind be|ne&s;actre&s;s,
Fathom uttered a groan, began
to &s;tir in the bed, and with a languid voice
