<P>The next &s;tep which Renaldo took for the
benefit of this wretched penitent, was to &s;end
for the apothecary with whom he left a &s;um
of money to be expended for the convenience
of Fathom and his wife; then he laid injunc|tions
upon the phy&s;ician to repeat his vi&s;its;
and that gentleman, together with the clergyman
and Jo&s;hua, taking leave of the others till next
