<P>The reader may well imagine the conver&s;a|tion
of the evening turned wholly upon the
&s;trange occurrence of the day, which &s;eemed
to have been concerted by &s;upernatural pre|&s;cience,
in order to &s;atisfy the vengeance, and
afford matter of triumph to the genero&s;ity of
tho&s;e who had been &s;o grievou&s;ly injured by the
<PB N="303" REF="304">
guilty Fathom. Tho' not one of them would
&s;ay that &s;uch a mi&s;creant ought to live; yet all
concurred in approving the offices of humanity
which had been performed, and even endea|voured
to find &s;pecious pretexts for vindicating
their compa&s;&s;ion. Don Diego &s;aid it would ill
